The paper deals with the analysis and manipulation of the dynamics of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) in order to understand and control their memory. This falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically in the subfield of neural networks. The paper discusses different training protocols, datasets, and architectures, indicating a focus on the practical application of RNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
